fields.title: Colorado Gives Day
fields.description:
***YOU NEED TO GET PERMISSIONS SHEETS SIGNED. EMAIL NIDESH AT nlamichhane@cherrycreekschools.org OR TEXT HIM AT 720-238-1270 TO GET A PERMISSION SHEET. BRING THE PERMISSION SHEET TO THE EVENT.*** 

Ask for Jill Henden or Louise Williams once you arrive.

The Cherry Creek Schools Foundation is hosting the annual Colorado Gives Day event at the Landmark.  The event is a reception to support the statewide Colorado Gives Day, an online day of giving supported by over 900 non-profits across the state.  This is the 3rd year the Foundation has participated and the money that is raised is used to support programs across the CCSD District that are in need of additional funding.

Duties will include: calling previous donors, thanking existing donors, and also helping with event logistics such as greeting guests and helping with set up and clean up.

fields.title: Sparkle Day!!!
fields.description:
It's time for our annual campus clean-up!

Join Mr. Silva, your school faculty members, and the NHS board at school on Friday, September 21st for a pancake breakfast in the morning followed by a group cleanup of the CCHS campus. This is a great way to get your community service hours early in the first semester while making a visible commitment to improving your school! Teachers have always given good feedback about this event so come do some community service that helps your own school!

Attendees should wear white t-shirts to identify them as NHS members.

*THIS IS AN NHS SPONSORED COMMUNITY SERVICE EVENT*

**Please arrive at 8:00 am if you would like to eat pancakes.**

fields.title: Derek's Dash 2013
fields.description:
*These hours count towards first semester- you **can** still do this if you already did your 4 summer hours* 

Derek's Dash is an annual 5k walk/run and silent auction to fight childhood epilepsy. 

This event is in honor of Derek Rudawsky, a student at CCHS, who suffers from Dravet Syndrome, a very serious and debilitating form of childhood epilepsy. All the money made from this event goes to research through the Dravet.org non-profit organization. The website for more information about the event is www.dereksdash.org. 

This event will be on August 18, 2013 at Cherry Creek Dam Road in Greenwood Village. 

We need 50 volunteers for this event over two shifts (25 per shift). You are more than welcome to sign up for both shifts. 

A free t-shirt, breakfast, and lunch will be provided. 

The shifts are:

6:00-8:30 AM

8:30-11:00 AM (this is the shift for which you are signing up)

fields.title: Diversity Conference
fields.description:
NHS memebrs will assist with closing activities and cleanup immediately following the conference from 4:00pm-7:00 pm on February 2. As an added bonus, if volunteers arrive by 3:30, they will have time to stop by the Fine Arts Theater to see our exciting closing band (but volunteers would need to report to the **Social Studies Resource Center** no later than 4:00pm). 

**If you can assist during this time period, please follow the instructions below:**

 1. Go to www.cherrycreekdiversity.org
 2. Click on the ‘Volunteer’ link
 3. Complete your contact information
 4. When the website asks for your specific volunteer code, type in: nhs (case sensitive)

Please register **NO LATER THAN** Friday, January 18, so that we will know if we have enough volunteers to fill this assigned time slot.

fields.title: Kids Bowl
fields.description:
**If you are signing up for this event, please email Pamela Rhoads at prhoads@twexp.org with your name, address, phone, and email information and ask for a waiver (you need one, details below). Let her know you are from CCHS NHS also. Here are the details:**

Students will score a touchdown by volunteering at this fun and exciting event featuring the Bronco Bounce House, Archery and Fly-fishing stations and activities throughout The Wildlife Experience museum. Other areas to assist are a scavenger hunt, helping kids make their own trail mix and a variety of crafts. Lunch is provided to all volunteers. Bring a water bottle to replenish!

**Volunteer Check-in:**  If you are scheduled for Shift I, please arrive at 8:15am. Enter the museum via the outside door next to the Boa Café. (Turn left at the crane sculpture in the middle of the courtyard. The door will be marked with signage). Take the staircase down to the registration area in the basement. 
 
**Event Waiver Form: If you are not a regular museum volunteer, you must sign a museum waiver. The waiver asks for contact and emergency information. Please bring this signed document with you on the day you volunteer. Please note, teens MUST have the form signed by a parent or guardian.   If you have school forms for me to sign, bring them with you and they will be returned with Mrs. Rhoads’ signature at the end of your shift.**
 
**Attire:**  **Please wear comfortable clothing and shoes.** You are encouraged to wear a favorite college or pro sports team sweatshirt or jersey of your favorite player. Or, if you have a school team shirt (football, basketball, golf shirt etc,) please wear it to add to the sports-themed atmosphere. If you don't have a sports shirt or a TWE uniform shirt, please wear a solid color shirt. (Green is great if you have one) and khaki pants. You will be provided with an event ID badge at registration.
 
**Job Stations:**  Job station assignments will be given to you at the volunteer registration table when you arrive.  If you are given an assignment you are not comfortable with just let me know.  Assignment examples include bounce house, sports games and activities, mascot stations and more.

Have a good time at this event everyone!

fields.title: After Prom
fields.description:
There are three different time slots for After Prom:

1. Friday, May 17, 2013 from 3:30 p.m.-10:30 p.m.
2. Saturday, May 18, 2013 from 9:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. 
3. Sunday, May 19, 2013 from 6:00 a.m.-11:00 a.m.

You do not need to be there for the entire shift (although you are welcome to be if you need the hours). Please specify on your event sheet the time you were there for; hours will get adjusted accordingly when they are put in.

**THERE IS A WEBSITE WHERE YOU *HAVE* TO SIGN UP FOR THE DIFFERENT SHIFTS:** [http://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0D4FA5A62FA31-cchs][1]

When you sign up, please make a note the time you will arrive and the length of time you can stay in the comment section. **We need this information for planning purposes.** Also add your phone number so we can contact you in the event that we finish early. Check in with the Volunteer Coordinator in Trophy Hall. They can sign your volunteer forms if necessary. 

***Food will be provided.***


  [1]: http://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0D4FA5A62FA31-cchs

fields.title: Ronald Mcdonald House
fields.description: This is the Aurora location and is a joint event with Big Sisters. Contact Katie Moore 720-854-5405 with any questions.

fields.description: Mrs. Goff would appreciate help in the Resource Center.

fields.title: 4th Quarter General Meeting
fields.description: The 4th quarter general meeting was held on Wednesday May 15 during periods 4, 5, and 6 in Shilinlaw.  If you could not attend please contact a board member or teacher sponsor for the information that you missed.  When you meet with the board member or sponsor please have with you a piece of paper with your full name, powerschool username, 3 causes that you want to work for next year, the name of a sport you are in (if applicable), and if you would be interested in tutoring athletes.  This meeting was MANDATORY so please meet with any of us so you remain in good standing with your hours.

fields.title: DCH Supplies Drive
fields.description: Members will receive **1 hour** of community service for dropping off at least 5 items during the duration of the event. All items donated will be given to Denver Children's Home, and therefore must be supplies which are recognized on the DCH needs list (attached and on Facebook post). Any additional items donated will be greatly appreciated, but will not allow you to gain more than 1 hour of service. Thank you for donating!

fields.title: East Building Pack-Up
fields.description:
The East Building faculty would greatly appreciate students to help pack-up their classrooms for the summer! Please report to the East building to see which teachers are in need of help. These hours can go toward summer hours or next year hours. This is a great way to get an early start on community service hours while helping those teachers in need!

On May 30th: Mrs. Brooks in West 304 would like students to help her.
On June 3rd: Mrs. Mckittrick in East 109 is looking for 3 to 4 students to come in to help. You can come in during the 5th period final if you do not have a class. Her room will be open from 10 a.m. and on.

fields.title: Charity Golf Tournament
fields.description: Volunteers needed at this charity event to benefit type 1 diabetes. Volunteer jobs include: tournament hosts, people to work at registration, and witnesses at prize holes. There will be 2 shifts: from 11:15am-1:30pm (8 volunteers) and 1:15-3:30pm (7 volunteers). Please dress appropriately and presentably for this tournament, as dress code is enforced.

fields.title: Courtyard Work
fields.description: Meet after school in the west building greenhouse courtyard. You will be helping Mr. Burns with clearing paths, overgrown planting beds, and removing remnants of construction materials to make it look good for back to school night.

fields.title: Back to School Night
fields.description: Come help hand out TCAP's to parents at Back to School Night. If you would like to volunteer, you **MUST** go see Mrs. Lupinetti in room W425 after you have RSVP'd and before Back to School Night to get your timeslot!

fields.title: Outdoor Adventure Fest
fields.description: The Wildlife Experience is eager to have Cherry Creek National Honor Society members volunteer at this event. The event has a rock climbing wall, a zip-line, bungee jumping activity, archery stations, and a bunch of food stations! Jobs will include working at the booths etc. There are two shifts: 8:30-1 and 12-5. If you are interested you MUST e-mail Pamela Rhoads at prhoads@twexp.org. She will send you information about what to wear and wear to meet as well as send you a waiver that you must have a parent sign in order to volunteer at this event.

fields.title: *Sparkle Day*
fields.description:
It's time for our annual campus clean-up!

Come help make Creek sparkle on Friday, September 20th!! This is a great way to get your community service hours early in the first semester while making a visible commitment to improving your school! Teachers have always given good feedback about this event so come do some community service that helps your own school!

Attendees should wear white t-shirts to identify them as NHS members.

*THIS IS AN NHS SPONSORED COMMUNITY SERVICE EVENT*
